description:
Hands on technician for startup, processing & maintaining our Injection Molding Machines and associated equipment;

Processing and handling of polypropylene;

Perform work as specified;

Analyze & repair machine issues as they arise;

Perform all preventative maintenance requirements for machines and related devices;

Maintain a safe & clean working environment by complying with procedures, rules & regulations. Document actions by completing maintenance and quality forms;

Verify that connected automated systems are set to regulation parameters;

As required, clean, smooth and position molds and cores;

Set-up and operate machines, read blueprints, and measure product with calipers;

Troubleshoot Injection Molding Machines and equipment;

Troubleshooting tasks might include, but not be limited to, analyzing faulty equipment, human error and preventing defects from occurring;

Operation of forklift as required;

Other related assignments as required;

SKILLS / QUALIFICATIONS

Manufacturing Experience, Manufacturing Quality, Safety Management, Quality Focus, Production Planning;

Independence, Reporting Skills, Automated Manufacturing.

Certification or experience in Electrical Technology, Mechanical Maintenance is desirable;

Prior experience with Injection Molding Equipment a plus. Hourly pay based on experience.'  
